.TH XCALENDAR 1 "2026-05-15" "User Commands" "CLI-Improved Manual"
.SH NAME
xcalendar \- list today's reminders
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xcalendar
.SH DESCRIPTION
A simple analogue of the BSD calendar utility.
.PP
The code for calendar is difficult to compile on modern hardware, due to antiquated libraries.  While not as fully-featured as the original, it gets the job done, and adds one glaring omission from the original.
.SH CALENDAR FILE
A file named \fB.calendar\fR must be present in your home directory.  Every line consists of a 
date indicator, followed by a tab and a reminder message.  Date indicators may consist of the following:
.TP
\fBMay 16\fR
A capitalized month name followed by the day of that month.
.TP
\fB05/16\fR
A month/day pair (American style).
.TP
\fB05-16\fR
A month-day pair (also American style).
.TP
\fBThursday\fR
A spelled out day name.
.TP
\fBThu\fR
A three-letter day name abbreviation.
\fbdaily\fR
The lowercase word "daily." Items marked with this will appear every day.
.SH INSTALLATION
Copy the script from the GitHub repository to your $PATH, typically /usr/local/bin.
